- **Main App Integration ([App.jsx](file:///C:/Users/julia/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ontoindex/src/App.jsx))**: Implemented simple token retrieval and state management. When a user logs in, the navigation dynamically transforms to include a "Dashboard" button.

## Verification & Usage Instructions

### Running the App Locally

1. **Start the Backend Node Server**
```bash
cd .\scratch\ontoindex\server\
npm run start
```

2. **Start the Frontend Vite Client**
```bash
cd .\scratch\ontoindex\
npm run dev
```

### Try it out!

1. Open your browser to the localhost port provided by Vite.
2. Click **Sign In** and then select **Create Account**.
3. Create a username and password (hashed automatically).
4. After signing in, navigate to the **Dashboard**.
5. Test the **Upload / Add Ontology** feature by adding a name and mock description, selecting the type of file mock if you desire.
6. Click the newly created Ontology block, and experiment with editing vocabulary terms natively on the web.
